{
  "Worker A completes a job in 5 days and Worker B completes it in 4 days. What is their combined work rate per day?": "",
  "4/5 per day": "",
  "9/20 per day": "",
  "5/4 per day": "",
  "1/9 per day": "",
  "Combined rate: 1/5 + 1/4 = 4/20 + 5/20 = 9/20 of the job per day.": "",
  "Pipe A fills a tank in 6 hours and Pipe B fills it in 9 hours. Together they fill it in:": "",
  "3 hours": "",
  "18/5 hours": "",
  "15 hours": "",
  "7.5 hours": "",
  "Combined rate: 1/6 + 1/9 = 3/18 + 2/18 = 5/18 of the tank per hour. Time = 1 / (5/18) = 18/5 = 3.6 hours.": "",
  "Two cars travel 120 miles. One goes 60 mph and the other goes 40 mph. What is the difference in their travel times?": "",
  "0.5 hours": "",
  "1.5 hours": "",
  "1 hour": "",
  "2 hours": "",
  "Time at 40 mph: 120/40 = 3 hours. Time at 60 mph: 120/60 = 2 hours. Difference: 3 − 2 = 1 hour.": "",
  "In a work-rate problem, if Person A finishes in a hours and Person B finishes in b hours, their combined rate is:": "",
  "a times b": "",
  "1/a + 1/b": "",
  "1/(a + b)": "",
  "a + b": "",
  "Each person's rate is the reciprocal of their individual time. The combined rate is the sum of the individual rates: 1/a + 1/b.": "",
  "Average cost per item equals:": "",
  "Total Cost times Number of items": "",
  "Revenue minus Total Cost": "",
  "Number of items / Total Cost": "",
  "Total Cost / Number of items": "",
  "Average cost per item is calculated by dividing the total cost by the number of items produced.": "",
  "A company's average cost is C(x) = (500 + 10x)/x. As x approaches infinity, C(x) approaches:": "",
  "500": "",
  "Infinity": "",
  "0": "",
  "$10": "",
  "Rewrite as 500/x + 10. As x grows large, 500/x approaches 0, so C(x) approaches $10. The fixed cost gets spread over more items.": "",
  "If a boat's speed in still water is b mph and the current is c mph, the upstream speed is:": "",
  "bc": "",
  "b/c": "",
  "b + c": "",
  "b − c": "",
  "Going upstream (against the current), the current slows the boat down, so the effective speed is b − c.": "",
  "If distance = rate times time, then time equals:": "",
  "Rate minus distance": "",
  "Distance times rate": "",
  "Distance / rate": "",
  "Rate / distance": "",
  "From d = rt, dividing both sides by r gives t = d/r.": "",
  "In a mixture problem, the amount of solute in a solution equals:": "",
  "Volume times concentration": "",
  "Volume plus concentration": "",
  "Volume divided by concentration": "",
  "Concentration minus volume": "",
  "The amount of solute equals the volume of the solution multiplied by its concentration (expressed as a decimal or fraction).": "",
  "Economies of scale means that average cost per unit _____ as production increases.": "",
  "Increases": "",
  "Doubles": "",
  "Stays the same": "",
  "Decreases": "",
  "Economies of scale occur because fixed costs are spread over more units as production increases, causing the average cost per unit to decrease.": "",
  "What is a work-rate problem?": "",
  "A problem where two or more entities work at individual rates to complete a shared task, modeled by 1/a + 1/b = 1/t": "",
  "A problem about the volume of containers": "",
  "A problem about calculating wages and hourly pay": "",
  "A problem about the speed of moving objects": "",
  "Work-rate problems involve combining individual rates (reciprocals of individual completion times) to find how long a shared task takes when entities work together.": "",
