  "A problem about mixing paint colors": "",
  "A problem where solutions of different concentrations are combined to achieve a target concentration": "",
  "A problem about combining rates of speed": "",
  "A problem that mixes addition and subtraction operations": "",
  "Mixture problems involve combining two or more solutions with known concentrations to create a final mixture with a desired concentration, using the equation: amount1 + amount2 = total amount.": "",
  "What does the formula d = rt represent?": "",
  "Demand equals revenue times tax": "",
  "Distance equals rate times time, the fundamental relationship in travel problems": "",
  "Depreciation equals rate times total": "",
  "Density equals resistance times temperature": "",
  "The formula d = rt relates distance, rate (speed), and time. It is the foundation for all distance-rate-time problems.": "",
  "What is average cost?": "",
  "Revenue minus expenses": "",
  "The price charged to customers": "",
  "The cost of the most expensive item": "",
  "Total cost divided by the number of items produced": "",
  "Average cost is the total cost of production divided by the number of units produced. It is modeled as a rational function when there are fixed costs.": "",
  "What are 'economies of scale'?": "",
  "The relationship between supply and demand": "",
  "A method for weighing items on a scale": "",
  "The increase in total cost as more items are produced": "",
  "The decrease in average cost per unit as production increases, because fixed costs are spread over more units": "",
  "Economies of scale describe the cost advantage of producing more units: as output grows, fixed costs (like rent and equipment) are divided among more items, lowering the per-unit cost.": "",
  "What is a rate in the context of word problems?": "",
  "The total amount of work completed": "",
  "The cost of a single item": "",
  "The difference between two measurements": "",
  "A quantity measured per unit of another quantity, such as jobs per hour or miles per hour": "",
  "A rate is a ratio that compares a quantity to a unit of time or another measure, such as miles per hour (speed) or jobs per hour (work rate).": "",
  "What is a combined rate?": "",
  "The average of two individual rates": "",
  "The product of two individual rates": "",
  "The sum of individual rates when multiple entities work simultaneously on the same task": "",
  "The faster of two individual rates": "",
  "When two or more entities work together, their individual rates add up. If A works at rate 1/a and B at rate 1/b, their combined rate is 1/a + 1/b.": "",
