  "What is a 'fixed cost' in a business context?": "",
  "A cost that changes depending on how many items are sold": "",
  "A cost that remains constant regardless of the number of items produced, such as rent or equipment": "",
  "The cost of raw materials per item": "",
  "The selling price of each item": "",
  "Fixed costs do not change with production volume. Examples include rent, insurance, and equipment purchases. In the average cost formula C(x) = (F + vx)/x, F represents the fixed cost.": "",
  "What is a 'variable cost'?": "",
  "The total cost of all production": "",
  "A cost that stays the same every month": "",
  "A cost that is unknown and must be solved for": "",
  "A cost that changes in proportion to the number of items produced, such as materials per item": "",
  "Variable costs increase proportionally with the number of units produced. Examples include raw materials, packaging, and direct labor per item.": "",
  "Two painters can paint a house together. Painter A can do it alone in 12 hours and Painter B can do it alone in 8 hours. How long do they take working together?": "",
  "6 hours": "",
  "10 hours": "",
  "20 hours": "",
  "24/5 hours (4.8 hours)": "",
  "Combined rate: 1/12 + 1/8 = 2/24 + 3/24 = 5/24 of the house per hour. Time = 1 / (5/24) = 24/5 = 4.8 hours.": "",
  "A pharmacist needs to mix a 15% acid solution with a 35% acid solution to get 500 mL of a 25% acid solution. How much of the 15% solution is needed?": "",
  "200 mL": "",
  "300 mL": "",
  "350 mL": "",
  "250 mL": "",
  "Let x = mL of 15% solution. Then 0.15x + 0.35(500 − x) = 0.25(500). Simplifying: 0.15x + 175 − 0.35x = 125, so −0.20x = −50 and x = 250 mL.": "",
  "A plane flies 600 miles with a 50 mph tailwind in the same time it would fly 400 miles against the wind. What is the plane's speed in still air?": "",
  "200 mph": "",
  "300 mph": "",
  "250 mph": "",
  "150 mph": "",
  "Set up 600/(p + 50) = 400/(p − 50). Cross-multiply: 600(p − 50) = 400(p + 50), giving 600p − 30000 = 400p + 20000, so 200p = 50000 and p = 250 mph.": "",
  "A company has fixed costs of $3000 and variable costs of $12 per item. How many items must be produced for the average cost per item to be $15?": "",
  "250 items": "",
  "1000 items": "",
  "750 items": "",
  "500 items": "",
  "Average cost: (3000 + 12x)/x = 15. Multiply by x: 3000 + 12x = 15x, so 3000 = 3x and x = 1000 items.": "",
  "A swimming pool has an inlet that fills it in 5 hours and a drain that empties it in 7 hours. If both are open, how long does it take to fill the pool?": "",
  "2/35 hours": "",
  "35/2 hours (17.5 hours)": "",
  "12 hours": "",
  "Net rate: 1/5 − 1/7 = 7/35 − 5/35 = 2/35 of the pool per hour. Time = 1 / (2/35) = 35/2 = 17.5 hours.": "",
  "Two machines package items. Machine A packages 200 items per hour and Machine B packages 150 items per hour. How long do they take together to package 1400 items?": "",
  "7 hours": "",
  "5 hours": "",
  "4 hours": "",
  "Combined rate: 200 + 150 = 350 items per hour. Time = 1400/350 = 4 hours.": "",
  "A cyclist rides 60 miles into a headwind and 60 miles back with a tailwind. The wind speed is 10 mph and the total round trip takes 8 hours. What is the cyclist's speed in still air?": "",
  "25 mph": "",
  "20 mph": "",
  "30 mph": "",
  "15 mph": "",
  "Set up 60/(c − 10) + 60/(c + 10) = 8. Multiply by (c − 10)(c + 10): 60(c + 10) + 60(c − 10) = 8(c² − 100), giving 120c = 8c² − 800. Rearranging: c² − 15c − 100 = 0, so (c − 20)(c + 5) = 0 and c = 20 mph.": "",
  "A lab technician adds pure water to 200 mL of a 60% salt solution to reduce it to a 40% concentration. How much water should be added?": "",
  "50 mL": "",
  "150 mL": "",
  "100 mL": "",
  "Salt amount stays constant: 0.60(200) = 120 mL. After adding w mL water: 120/(200 + w) = 0.40, so 120 = 80 + 0.40w, giving 0.40w = 40 and w = 100 mL.": "",
  "A small business has total costs C(x) = 2000 + 15x dollars, where x is the number of items produced. How many items must be produced for the average cost per item to reach $25?": "",
  "100 items": "",
  "200 items": "",
  "150 items": "",
  "Average cost: (2000 + 15x)/x = 25. Multiply by x: 2000 + 15x = 25x, so 2000 = 10x and x = 200 items.": "",
  "Three workers can complete a project individually. Worker A finishes in 10 days, Worker B in 15 days, and Worker C in 30 days. How long does it take all three working together?": "",
  "18.3 days": "",
  "3 days": "",
  "10 days": "",
  "5 days": "",
  "Combined rate: 1/10 + 1/15 + 1/30 = 3/30 + 2/30 + 1/30 = 6/30 = 1/5 of the project per day. Time = 1 / (1/5) = 5 days.": ""
